 The A Cry A Smile A Dance hitmaker confirmed last year that she was divorced from her now ex-husband Siphiwe Mhlambi but would not be drawn into divulging details.For the first time since going through the split Judith has opened up in a True Love interview about why she and her ex-husband decided to keep their divorce out of the spotlight. We tried to keep the media out of it to protect ourselves and the children. There s no bad blood between Siphiwe and I she said.The singer explained that just because people are divorced doesn t mean they hate each other .Judith also looks incredible after shedding all those unwanted kilos.The singer embarked on her weight loss journey last year and has been documenting her process on social media.She has also recently released a gospel album My Worship (Live) after having made a smooth transition from being known as a jazz artist.